metadata.name: Alien Blobs
metadata.description:
It is said that were we to encounter life elsewhere in the universe, it may come in a form that is completely unfamiliar to us here on Earth.  This generative token creates structures which resemble alien blobs flying their environment.  Perhaps they live in some atmospheric anomaly of a planet, or perhaps they simply represent the strangeness of possible life out there in the unknown. Regardless, they do fly up unsettlingly for a few seconds before the token settles on the final image for that viewscreen size.  Larger viewscreen is recommended to see a more biological feel to it.  The collectible features of this NFT are: 

ColorScheme: red-purple (common), orange-yellow (common), purple (~10%), red (~10%)
ShapeScheme: tall (~10%), wide (~5%), circle (common) 

the ColorScheme and ShapeScheme determine dominant overall features in the tokens having those features.

metadata.name: life
metadata.description:
Generate life with your unique token!
 
This is a variant of the famous "Game of Life" using different colors for longer living cells. Variations also include rounded or squared shapes. 

Basic JavaScript Code:

for(c=[d=b*b];d--;c[d]=e==3
||a[d]&&e==2)e=a[d-b-1]+a[d
-b]+a[d-b+1]+a[d-1]+a[d+1]+
a[d+b-1]+a[d+b]+a[d+b+1];

metadata.name: Candles
metadata.description:
Why are you into NFT's? Chasing the profit or loving the art? The "Candles" project arises from this dilemma.

Once you mint, the market will open and randomly decide whether you win or lose. 
There is Dark and Light Mode and very rarely you will mint a Single Loop Trader Mode piece, which is by far the dullest version, and at the same time the rarest and so the most valuable... 
So question yourself, would I rather mint a dull and valuable piece, or a colorful piece of art to enjoy.

And oh, If you press "r" you will be able to see your profit (or loss) and toggle it on/off. just for fun :-)

@Elum0x, pure Javascript, Brussels 2022.

metadata.name: GridWorks
metadata.description:
Inspired by grid-based geometric artworks, GridWorks is a collection of 250 pieces, where I experimented with various layouts, shapes, colors and rotations.

I've always loved geometry and geometric shapes, as it never ceases to amaze me how one can achieve quite unpredictable and complex results just by simple variations, alignments and rotations. And in GridWorks, I wanted to add my touch to the popular grid-based geometric art concept with a high variety of shapes, visually pleasing combinations and vibrant colors.

GridWorks is generated with 60 different hand-coded base shapes, 18 delicately prepared color palettes and a number of varying features, resulting in a countless amount of unique variations.

* * *

Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
Made with: JavaScript + HTML Canvas
License: LICENSE.txt

metadata.name: Acid Crystals
metadata.description:
Acid Crystals is an algorithm that generates psychedelic gemstones.  It models a randomly generated crystal structure in 3D that reflects faceted images of a natural scene to the viewer.  Each scene is described by the ‘Zone’ feature.  Huge thanks to Greg Zaal for releasing these amazing equirectangular photos using the CC0 license on Poly Haven!  The ‘Density’ and ‘Temperature’ features drive the crystal geometry generation and background color selection respectively.

If you look at individual LSD-25 crystals under a sufficiently powerful microscope while high on the exact same batch of acid, you’ll see something very much like this.

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: Pixel Blobs II
metadata.description:
This is a "zero player game" partially inspired by Conway's Game of Life. Between 4-10 pixel blobs are places on a screen and autonomously grow based on a deterministic set of rules. The game ends when all of the available cells are occupied by a blob. Some blobs prefer to slowly expand evenly in every direction. Other blobs prefer to aggressively push all of their energy into a single direction gobbling up as much territory as possible.

There is no single "victory condition". Maybe you care about the conquest of a single blob controlling as much space or energy as possible. Or maybe you prefer blobs to collaborate to create beautiful chaotic patterns.

Controls:
- 's' Saves a PNG of the current screen.
- 'i' Restarts the game in "infinite mode". 10 seconds after each game ends, the rules are shuffled and the game resets.

metadata.name: Figment
metadata.description:
"Figment" is my first artistic generative AI project, these are noise hallucinations of a neural network!


The first tokens will be airdropped to the original minters of ACCUMULATOR (one each), the rest will be a dutch auction starting from 5 to 1 tez, in 30 minutes intervals (5,4,3,2,1)

The auction will start on Saturday (March 19) at 9:00 UTC


The sequential model for this nn is composed of 3 dense layers, and has been trained for up to 74 epochs with 11 different datasets:

=======================================
Layer 1 [Dense, 50, tanh] 2550  (input)
_______________________________________
Layer 2 [Dense, 50, tanh] 2550 (hidden)

The auction will start on Saturday (March 19) at 9:00 UTC

metadata.name: Bellissimas
metadata.description:
Expressive portraits inspired by @michelepetrelli 

The used techniques search in the unexplored field of mixing pfp layer based work and real-time generative algorithms changing and adding to the premade assets.

The pre-generated assets include original artworks by Petrelli, Imitations of Petrelli's work by @brutalisti, GAN generated artworks inspired by Petrelli using several different AI technologies.

Every generatively chosen layer combination is live-processed and generatively altered in aspects of color and shape. Then the generative algorithm proceed with captured color palettes and generate background and additional drawing over and under the initial layers. The final result as acquired by visualizing everything with live generative algorithm that give additional layer of uniqueness.

Project by  @michelepetrelli & @brutalisti, curated by XCOLLABS
